                        <p class="col_about_p">Due to this increase, Google has started ranking websites based on their mobile-friendliness too. A website is not good enough if it does not respond well to mobile phones. Therefore a good website should be responsive to modern smartphones. </p>
                        <p class="col_about_p">Mobile optimization requires a few basic steps:-</p>
                        <p class="col_about_p"><li>Use a ‘responsive’ theme for your website. Nowadays, most templates and themes available online are suitable for mobile phones. </li></p>
                        <p class="col_about_p"><li>The graphics used should not be too large in size. Unnecessarily large files take more time to load on phones and this could decrease user retention on your site.  </li></p>
                        <p class="col_about_p"><li>Clickable links and buttons should be added properly keeping in mind the small screen of mobile phones. </li></p>
                        <p class="text_bold">Technical SEO</p>
